{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf6998153-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"13103"},"text":"§ 13103.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Program acceptance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf6998154-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary shall make a contract with, and allocate and distribute amounts from the Sport Fish Restoration and Boating Trust Fund established by section 9504 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s9504"},"text":"26 U.S.C. 9504","children":[],"tail":") to, a State that has an approved State recreational boating safety program, if the State demonstrates to the Secretary’s satisfaction that—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf6998155-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the program submitted by that State is consistent with this chapter and chapters 61 and 123 of this title;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf6998156-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" amounts distributed will be used to develop and carry out a State recreational boating safety program containing the minimum requirements of subsection (c) of this section;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf6998157-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" sufficient State matching amounts are available from general State revenue, undocumented vessel numbering and license fees, State marine fuels taxes, or from a fund constituted from the proceeds of those taxes and established to finance a State recreational boating safety program; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf6998158-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the program submitted by that State designates a State lead authority or agency that will carry out or coordinate carrying out the State recreational boating safety program supported by financial assistance of the United States Government in that State, including the requirement that the designated State authority or agency submit required reports that are necessary and reasonable to carry out properly and efficiently the program and that are in the form prescribed by the Secretary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf6998159-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Amounts of the Government (except amounts from sources referred to in subsection (a)(3) of this section) may not be used to provide a State’s share of the costs of the program described under this section. State matching amounts committed to a program under this chapter may not be used to constitute the State’s share of matching amounts required by another program of the Government.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf699815a-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary shall approve a State recreational boating safety program, and the program is eligible to receive amounts authorized to be expended under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s13107"},"text":"section 13107 of this title","children":[],"tail":", if the program includes—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf699815b-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a vessel numbering system approved or carried out by the Secretary under chapter 123 of this title;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf699815c-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a cooperative boating safety assistance program with the Coast Guard in that State;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf699815d-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" sufficient patrol and other activity to ensure adequate enforcement of applicable State boating safety laws and regulations;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf699815e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/c/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an adequate State boating safety education program, that includes the dissemination of information concerning the hazards of operating a vessel when under the influence of alcohol or drugs; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idf699815f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/c/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a system, approved by the Secretary, for reporting marine casualties required under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s6102"},"text":"section 6102 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf6998160-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s13103/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary’s approval under this section is a contractual obligation of the Government for the payment of a proportionate share of the cost of carrying out the program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf6998161-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/89"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–89","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-08-26"},"text":"Aug. 26, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/97/593"},"text":"97 Stat. 593","children":[],"tail":", § 13102; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dA/tX/s1011/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. A, title X, § 1011(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1013"},"text":"98 Stat. 1013","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/557/s7/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–557, § 7(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/2862"},"text":"98 Stat. 2862","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/307/s1/17"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–307, § 1(17)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-05-19"},"text":"May 19, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/446"},"text":"100 Stat. 446","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/626/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–626, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-07"},"text":"Nov. 7, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3505"},"text":"100 Stat. 3505","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/448/s6/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–448, § 6(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":"–(5), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-09-28"},"text":"Sept. 28, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1840"},"text":"102 Stat. 1840","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/595/tIII/s312/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–595, title III, § 312(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-16"},"text":"Nov. 16, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/2987"},"text":"104 Stat. 2987","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/59/tX/s10141"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–59, title X, § 10141","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/1931"},"text":"119 Stat. 1931","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 13103 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304","children":[],"tail":", §§ 15(25), 16(b)(1), (c)(4), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1704-1706"},"text":"120 Stat. 1704–1706","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf6998162-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf6998163-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idf6998164-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:thead","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{"colspan":"2"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Revised section","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:th","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:i","attrib":{},"text":"Source section (U.S. Code)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tbody","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"13102","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"46:1475","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 13102(a) authorizes the Secretary to contract with the States and allocate the amounts of them if they demonstrate to the satisfaction of the Secretary that they have a program consistent with this chapter and chapters 61 and 123, that the amounts received will be used to develop and carry out their recreational boating safety and facilities improvement programs, that they have sufficient matching amounts available from specified revenue sources to meet the objectives of the program, that they will submit required reports to the Secretary to ensure continued compliance with the objectives of this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (b) prohibits a State from using any other funds received from the Federal Government to meet their required State match.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsections (c) and (d) require the Secretary to approve a State’s recreational boating safety and facilities improvement program if the program meets the specified requirements of this subsection.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (e) makes the approval of a State’s program a contractual obligation of the Government to pay the Federal portion of the cost to carry out the program.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (f) allows a State to submit a combined boating safety and facility improvement program if it meets the requirements of all of the objectives of both programs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf6998165-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idf6998166-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 13103 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s13104"},"text":"section 13104 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf6998167-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s16/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 16(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s13102"},"text":"section 13102 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s15/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 15(25)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s9504"},"text":"26 U.S.C. 9504","children":[],"tail":")” after “Internal Revenue Code of 1986”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s16/c/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 16(c)(4)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 13107” for “section 13106”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2005—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/59"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–59","children":[],"tail":" substituted “the Sport Fish Restoration and Boating Trust Fund” for “the Boat Safety Account” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/595/s312/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–595, § 312(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “State” after “general”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/595/s312/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–595, § 312(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or drugs” after “alcohol”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/595/s312/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–595, § 312(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a proportionate share” for “the proportional share”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/448/s6/b/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–448, § 6(b)(4)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “1986” for “1954.” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/448/s6/b/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–448, § 6(b)(5)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (4) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (4) read as follows: “the program submitted by that State designates a State lead authority or agency that will carry out or coordinate carrying out out the State recreational boating safety program supported by financial assistance of the United States Government in that State, including the requirement that the designated State authority or agency submit required reports that are necessary and reasonable to carry out properly and efficiently the program and that are in the form prescribed by the Secretary.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/448/s6/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–448, § 6(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “(except amounts from” for “from sources (except”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/626/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–626, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Boat Safety Account established by section 9504 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1954.” for “Fund established under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s13107"},"text":"section 13107 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/626/s4/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–626, § 4(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “out” after “carrying”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/307"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–307","children":[],"tail":" substituted “carrying out the State” for “carrying the State”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s1011/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 1011(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), in provisions preceding par. (1) substituted “shall” for “may” and struck out “and facilities improvement” after “boating safety”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s1011/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 1011(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (3), struck out “, (d), or (f)” after “requirements of subsection (c)” and struck out “and facilities improvement” after “boating safety”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3), (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s1011/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 1011(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “and facilities improvement” after “boating safety”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/557"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–557","children":[],"tail":" inserted provisions relating to dissemination of information concerning the hazards of operating a vessel when under the influence of alcohol."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (d), (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s1011/c/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 1011(c)(4)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (e) as (d). Former subsec. (d), which related to approval of a State recreational boating facilities improvement program by the Secretary, was struck out."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s1011/c/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 1011(c)(4)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (f) which related to submission by a State to the Secretary of a combined program for the improvement of recreational boating safety and recreational boating facilities."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idf6998168-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf6998169-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2005 Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"From ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-08-10"},"text":"Aug. 10, 2005","children":[],"tail":", to end of fiscal year 2005, subsec. (a) of this section considered to read as immediately before enactment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/59"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–59","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/74/s101/b"},"text":"section 101(b) of Pub. L. 109–74","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s777b"},"text":"section 777b of Title 16","children":[],"tail":", Conservation."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","childre